responseText: NSLOCTEXT("[70199B914E7E03A9706A1499CF20B1FD]", "02515F70460C49E79F9E82A927F39004", "When the Verran equinox approaches and the sun sets beyond the colorful foliage of the Crystalbough Forest, it\'s difficult to discern where the treetops end and the sky begins. The trees of the Crystalbough are all of the same species: thin-leaved, crystalline hardwoods with silver-white bark. As the sun sets, their turning leaves of orange, yellow, and red blend seamlessly with the fiery colors of the sky, while motes of Essence-charged particles dance in the waning rays of golden light.")
